human-authorized amend #2 (interactive). SCEN-005/006 corrected: the optimizer config surface is nitro.vercel.config.images (NOT packages/ui-*/vercel.json, which is inert/schema-only). Root cause: @nuxt/image 1.11.0 providerSetup.vercel hardcodes formats:[webp,avif]+minimumCacheTTL:300 and writes nuxt.options.nitro.vercel.config.images via defu (our explicit nitro config wins). Runtime proof: SCEN-009b preview served avif + max-age=2592000. Evidence: scenarios/.amends/nuxt-image-1.11.0-vercel-providerSetup.evidence.txt. base_head=3d9314717f807729b2c287fb4d0d1dd0dcd2fbdf base_file_sha256=e29029503012c778a8d67dea80f5d5fbed516443438cdbe3c899ba1f0184b320
amend #3 (same base HEAD 3d93147, human-authorized): defu 6.1.4 CONCATENATES arrays (proven) → a plain nitro.vercel.config.images cannot win formats over @nuxt/image's hardcoded [webp,avif]. Mechanism corrected to a hooks['nitro:config'] override (post-module, beats defu concat). SCEN-005/006 now assert the EFFECTIVE merged images config (defu(@nuxt/image-1.11.0 defaults)+hook override, replicated in-test) — would have caught the defu-concat class. Evidence: scenarios/.amends/nuxt-image-1.11.0-vercel-providerSetup.evidence.txt + empirical defu test in session.
